<div class="reportSection">
  <h4>Population<a href="#" data-toggle-node="54d9796efa94e697759d0a86" data-visible="false">show layer</a></h4>
  <p class="large">The total population of the countries within the sketch is <strong>{{numpeople}}</strong>, which is <strong>{{percpeople}}%</strong> of the population within the PACIOCEA region.
  </p>
    <div><a class="details" href="#">show details</a>
    <div class="hidden">
      <p>
		Rapid population growth characterizes the region and has doubled since 1975 and is expected to double again by 2050. This is mainly due to Papua New Guinea’s, Solomon’s and Vanuatu’s rapid population increase rates. Papua New Guinea represents 70% of the total of the PICTs population in 2013.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="reportSection tableContainer">
