      <p>
		Emigration acts as a major driving force in Polynesia and Micronesia and explains their slowest growth, whereas Melanesia is lacking emigration possibilities. In 2010, about 850 000 Pacific-born people (or from Pacific ethnic-descent) lived in Pacific Rim countries (New Zealand, Australia, USA, Canada, with Asia being of increasing importance). This is more than the total population of Micronesia or Polynesia and it has real impact on national economies through remittances that can represent close to 30% of the GDP for some countries.
      </p>
